OL,6,FAssistant Commissioner Matt Twist has
OL,7,Falso written to Mr Falter, offering
OL,8,Fhim a private meeting "to both
OL,9,Fapologise to him personally and
OL,10,Fdiscuss what more the Met can do to
OL,11,Fensure Jewish Londoners feel safe".
OL,13,FBoth Mr Falter and former home
OL,14,Fsecretary Suella Braverman called for
OL,15,FSir Mark to go, accusing him of
OL,16,F"emboldening" antisemites by failing
OL,17,Fto curtail the now regular marches
OL,18,Fthrough the capital.
